\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Patti:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::1> Patti has resigned herself to the fact that Evan is convinced that Sarah is the one for him. Although she is still concerned that his heart will get broken, she has decided to support him. In this scene, she shares her conversation with Evan and encourages them to support Evan and Sarah\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92s relationship like he would have if the situation were reversed. She plans to support him and be there if things go south.<!$Scr_Cs::1>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Guido:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::1> Guido wants no part of this drama. It doesn\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92t matter to him who Evan is in a relationship with. He wants to get home and drink the beer that Evan had brought the whole group as a thank you for volunteering. <!$Scr_Cs::1>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Roxanne:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::1> Roxanne is unmoved by Patti\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92s words. She thinks that Patti and Evan should be together and has predetermined that she doesn\u8217\'92t like Sarah and never will. However, for Patti\u8217\'92s sake, she has agreed to bite her lip in the future with Sarah around and to avoid her passive aggressiveness around Sarah. <!$Scr_Cs::1>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Group of friends:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::1> The consensus of the rest of the friends is that they did what they felt they had to do and at least attempted to caution Evan about Sarah. They are satisfied that Patti accomplished that goal and ready to let it all go and support Evan. Once Patti\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92s done talking, they share Guido\u8217\'92s enthusiasm for a drive home for a night of partying.<!$Scr_Cs::1><!$Scr_Ps::4>}
